If you can't beat them, they're not properly tied down :)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ureverance.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reverance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/12/01 1:25:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My thoughts on A.O. so far</span><hr size=1> I've also been playing AO.  Jaelis, 10th level Soldier of Omni, is my char if you stop in and wanna say hi.  I'll put up a few things about it also in the future.  The only complaint I have right now is the lag.  I get dropped &quot;zoning&quot; (although it's not really zoning) from time to time, populated areas are NUTS to try and there are times when you can't do anything for about 2 mins (but I've found that you can still chat through /tells during this time which I thought was strange).  Other than that, for being a newly released game, it's not too bad.  I'm not huge on the futuristic genre, which is why I can't wait for DAoC!!!, but it's pretty cool...if you can look beyond the aggrivating lag. <p><FONT color=0066FF>Reverance Echoblade<BR></FONT color>
<FONT color=FFFF99>Bard of the 54th song<BR></FONT color>
<FONT color=lightgoldenrod>Crusader of Justice</FONT color></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uratdm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ratdm</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/15/01 1:25:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My thoughts on A.O. so far</span><hr size=1> Well they've fixed the mission bug so I'm back to playing my agent.  Right now he is lvl 7, I just bought a Stigma Rifle and have found that it helps to no end.  Right now I am not sure what to do and am currently thinking of leaving eq <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  while I wouldn't remove myself from the guild I probably wouldn't be on much. <p>-Deluwen Blackguard

If you can't beat them, they're not properly tied down :)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/bphoenixrisen50946.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=brinnay>Brinnay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/16/01 1:46:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My thoughts on A.O. so far.....</span><hr size=1> Are that when its playable, it is awesome.  I have had several play sessions that have lasted 4 to 5 hours at a time with no discos.  I have also had several days where I just gave up in frustration.<br>
My main concern is the longevity of the game.  The current level cap is 200, and I have seen several in the 50's already.  This game is supposed to have a lifespan of 4 years, and I am betting that there will be some a 200 within 2 maybe 3 months.  The game is supposed to be story driven, but what is the point if you have already gotten to 200?  There has been talk of raising the level cap though.<br>
<br>
As for the game itself, I love it.  I really, really like the whole concept of missions, and being able to equip yourself by choosing what missions you go on.  <br>
The other great thing is you don't have to group.  You can get xp on your own, but if you choose to group, you get somewhere around 75% of the xp for the critter.  So say you kill a critter that is worth 100 xp.  If you kill it solo, you get 100 xp.  If you are in a 6 person group, everyone in the group gets around 75 or so xp.  Unlike eq, where everyone gets around 16 xp.  (this is not exact on my part, and it assumes that everyone is around the same level)<br>
<br>
So if any of you are playing and want to chat or whatever, give me a tell.  I'm either Gosling, a lvl 13 ish neutral Enforcer, or Solarine, lvl 8 Omni Tek Martial Artist (currently stuck somewhere in Omni 1)<br>
<br>
See you all later!<br>
<br>
Brinnay<br>
