I have been experimenting with several different characters lately, if I had stuck with one I would be level 50 or so.  I don't mind just fooling around in this game because it is a ton of fun.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uratdm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ratdm</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/11/01 2:16:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My thoughts on A.O. so far</span><hr size=1> Well it's time for another update.  Ok I've gotten Ratdm up to level 26 and participated in my first player run event.  The event was a pvp event run by a level 88 named Magika, it was called Fight Night.  There were several division 1-9, 10-19, 20-29 and some higher devision that i don't know the levels of.  By the time sign up had ended there were around 50-75 people huddled around the areana watching.  There were at least 5 players in every group.  The event lasted around 5 hours with several delays due to people getting in the ring when they weren't supposed to.  <br>
<br>
This was my first experience with pvp in AO and I wise quite nervous when I was called to fight a lvl 23 soldier in my first fight.  After about 30-45 seconds of battle I won.  The match was double disqualification so he still had another chance later on.  For the next 2 hours or so I watched other matches, and generally had a pretty good time.  After a while my next match comes up, and I end up fighting somebody three levels higher than me a level 29 martial artist.  I was nervous and apearently for good reason.  The match starts out and its going fairly evenly i'm at about half health and cast my MK reflect shield (it makes it so i only take 25% damage and the attacker takes 75% for about 15-20 seconds.  Well as I'm casting this he uses his dimach on me.  Dimach is the equivelent of harm touch except maybe a little better.  at my lvl i have around 600 hp and was at about 300 when he used it.  Instant toast, 390 or so points of damage.  Luckily as said before I have two chances.  After getting back to the arena I watched for another hour or so before everybody who had lost in my devision duked it out in battle royale.  I was the winner of that, both me and the soldier took out the beurocrat and then i took out the soldier.  So now its just me and taewandoe (i think thats what his name was) Round two I win with a deflect shield and his not using dimach.  Round three to determine the winner of the 20-29 devision he dimachs my reflect sheild when we were both at half health frying himself for 290 pts of damage.  I won the devision championship and was awarded 30k credits and a pair of ql 129 omni pol elite boots.  It was quite a bit of fun. <p>-Deluwen Blackguard

If you can't beat them, they're not properly tied down :)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uratdm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ratdm</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/29/01 2:07:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My thoughts on A.O. so far</span><hr size=1> Well seams like its time for an update mostly because I had a good day yesterday.  Ratdm is now lvl 36 he has 600 in the main ac's, a ql 60 stigma rifle, 700k credits, his freshman title (once your pvp kills is 10 higher than losses you get this i think my pvp record is 11-1 or 13-1 not sure).  I had a very good day yesterday I made around 50k credits, went on an invasion of mmd (this is where most of the pvp takes place at the moment) and managed to get a car in a mission chest ( its super low ql but damn it's a car <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  I seriously doubt that I will be returning to eq, I always found the game much to long and boring, I also never had good enough equipment among many other things.  Stability has increase quite a bit but its still not as good as eq.  Pvp is fun but some classes are really really bad at it (meta).  So far I really like what I'm seeing.  If you anybody plays send me a tell <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I wish you all good luck and will probably update you every once in awhile. <p>-Deluwen Blackguard

